         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>NEX17/14 MetroFutures Rolling Stock Replacement Programme</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>DN245952</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="60210000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>As part of its MetroFutures programme, Nexus wishes to procure a new fleet of light rail electric multiple units (New Fleet) to replace its existing Metrocar fleet (Existing Fleet), a maintainer for the new and existing fleets and new depot facilities. The successful bidder will be responsible for the design, construction, testing, and delivery of the New Fleet pursuant to a Manufacturing and Supply Agreement (MSA). It will enter into one or more train services agreements (TSAs) for maintenance of the Existing Fleet until removed from service and for long-term maintenance of the New Fleet including heavy/light maintenance and daily servicing for the design life of the New Fleet. It will provide trains to Nexus (as Metro operator) that are ready and safe for entry into service each day. The successful bidder will also be required to design, construct and deliver new maintenance facilities under a Depot Construction Agreement (DCA).</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">500000000.00</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="34622400"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45234112"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKC2"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>As above.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>This procurement is subject to approval/funding. Nexus reserves the right, at its discretion, to award the MSA and an associated technical support and spares supply agreement and to proceed with the purchase of the New Fleet from the successful bidder, but not to award either of the TSAs or the DCA. It also reserves the right to conduct separate procurements in relation to the TSAs and the DCA.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-05-31</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>Nexus is conducting a market consultation in relation to this procurement. Bidders interested in participating in the consultation should register and access a questionnaire on the NEPO procurement portal (www.nepo.org). Responses to the questionnaire must be submitted by midday on 8 March 2018. Submissions made after this date will not be considered. Following the issue of its OJEU Contract Notice (expected late May 2018), Nexus will hold a market day for potential bidders and will provide further information in relation to the opportunity. This is likely to be held in early to mid June 2018 at a time/location to be confirmed in Newcastle or the surrounding area. Potential bidders will be invited to register their interest in the opportunity via the NEPO procurement portal and further details about this will be provided with the issuing of the OJEU Contract Notice. Direct invitations to the market day will only be issued to those parties formally registering their interest via NEPO.</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-01-23</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
         </COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
